        public java.util.Set<IntRange> asRanges()
        Description copied from interface: IntRangeSet
        Returns a view of the disconnected ranges that make up this range set. The returned set may be empty. The iterators returned by its Iterable.iterator() method return the ranges in increasing order of lower bound (equivalently, of upper bound).

      • add

        public void add(IntRange rangeToAdd)
        Description copied from interface: IntRangeSet
        Adds the specified range to this IntRangeSet (optional operation). That is, for equal range sets a and b, the result of a.add(range) is that a will be the minimal range set for which both a.enclosesAll(b) and a.encloses(range).

        Note that range will be coalesced with any ranges in the range set that are connected with it. Moreover, if range is empty, this is a no-op.

        Specified by:
        add in interface IntRangeSet

      • remove

        public void remove(IntRange rangeToRemove)
        Description copied from interface: IntRangeSet
        Removes the specified range from this IntRangeSet (optional operation). After this operation, if range.contains(c), this.contains(c) will return false.

        If range is empty, this is a no-op.

        Specified by:
        remove in interface IntRangeSet

      • complement

        public IntRangeSet complement()
        Description copied from interface: IntRangeSet
        Returns a view of the complement of this IntRangeSet.

        The returned view supports the IntRangeSet.add(org.datavec.dataframe.util.collections.IntRange) operation if this IntRangeSet supports IntRangeSet.remove(org.datavec.dataframe.util.collections.IntRange), and vice versa.

      • subRangeSet

        public IntRangeSet subRangeSet(IntRange view)
        Description copied from interface: IntRangeSet
        Returns a view of the intersection of this IntRangeSet with the specified range.

        The returned view supports all optional operations supported by this IntRangeSet, with the caveat that an IllegalArgumentException is thrown on an attempt to add any range not enclosed by view.

      • clear

        public void clear()
        Description copied from interface: IntRangeSet
        Removes all ranges from this IntRangeSet (optional operation). After this operation, this.contains(c) will return false for all c.

        This is equivalent to remove(IntRange.all()).

        Specified by:
        clear in interface IntRangeSet

      • enclosesAll

        public boolean enclosesAll(IntRangeSet other)
        Description copied from interface: IntRangeSet
        Returns true if for each member range in other there exists a member range in this range set which encloses it. It follows that this.contains(value) whenever other.contains(value). Returns true if other is empty.

        This is equivalent to checking if this range set IntRangeSet.encloses(org.datavec.dataframe.util.collections.IntRange) each of the ranges in other.

        Specified by:
        enclosesAll in interface IntRangeSet

      • addAll

        public void addAll(IntRangeSet other)
        Description copied from interface: IntRangeSet
        Adds all of the ranges from the specified range set to this range set (optional operation). After this operation, this range set is the minimal range set that encloses both the original range set and other.

        This is equivalent to calling IntRangeSet.add(org.datavec.dataframe.util.collections.IntRange) on each of the ranges in other in turn.

        Specified by:
        addAll in interface IntRangeSet

      • removeAll

        public void removeAll(IntRangeSet other)
        Description copied from interface: IntRangeSet
        Removes all of the ranges from the specified range set from this range set (optional operation). After this operation, if other.contains(c), this.contains(c) will return false.

        This is equivalent to calling IntRangeSet.remove(org.datavec.dataframe.util.collections.IntRange) on each of the ranges in other in turn.

        Specified by:
        removeAll in interface IntRangeSet

      • intersects

        public boolean intersects(IntRange otherRange)
        Description copied from interface: IntRangeSet
        Returns true if there exists a non-empty range enclosed by both a member range in this range set and the specified range. This is equivalent to calling subRangeSet(otherRange) and testing whether the resulting range set is non-empty.
        Specified by:
        intersects in interface IntRangeSet
